<!-- Wasm -->
<section id="wasm" class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-pinky-50/50">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-center mb-3 sm:mb-4">WebAssembly Nativo</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-500 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8 sm:mb-12 text-sm sm:text-lg font-light">Emiss&atilde;o direta <code>.wasm</code> - sem Emscripten, sem wabt.js, sem LLVM.</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <div>
        <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">XS</div>
          <pre class="p-4 text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto"><span class="kw">CHAMA ESSE CARA</span> <span class="fn">sum</span>(a, b) {
  <span class="kw">VOLTA</span> a + b
}
<span class="kw">CHAMA ESSE CARA</span> <span class="fn">main</span>() {
  <span class="kw">VOLTA</span> sum(<span class="num">10</span>, <span class="num">20</span>)
}</pre>
        </div>
        <div data-cmd="xs build --wasm math.xs" class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-sm text-gray-500 cursor-pointer transition-all hover:border-pinky-400 hover:shadow-sm select-none">
          <span class="text-pinky-400">$</span>
          <span class="text-gray-800">xs build --wasm math.xs</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4"><strong class="text-gray-800">wasm_binary.js</strong> implementa a especifica&ccedil;&atilde;o do formato bin&aacute;rio Wasm do zero:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1.5 mb-4">
          <li>N&uacute;mero m&aacute;gico (<code>00 61 73 6d</code>) + vers&atilde;o (<code>01 00 00 00</code>)</li>
          <li>Codifica&ccedil;&atilde;o de se&ccedil;&otilde;es: Se&ccedil;&atilde;o Type (assinaturas de fun&ccedil;&atilde;o), Se&ccedil;&atilde;o Function (mapeamento de &iacute;ndice de tipo), Se&ccedil;&atilde;o Code (corpos de fun&ccedil;&atilde;o com declara&ccedil;&otilde;es locais), Se&ccedil;&atilde;o Export (exporta&ccedil;&otilde;es nomeadas), Se&ccedil;&atilde;o Data (conte&uacute;do inicial da mem&oacute;ria)</li>
          <li>Todos os inteiros codificados via LEB128 (variantes unsigned e signed)</li>
          <li>Sistema de tipos de dois valores: <code>i32</code> e <code>f64</code> - todas as opera&ccedil;&otilde;es aritm&eacute;ticas XS mapeiam para o opcode apropriado</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">O <strong class="text-gray-800">linker</strong> interno resolve &iacute;ndices de fun&ccedil;&atilde;o entre se&ccedil;&otilde;es durante uma segunda passagem. Ap&oacute;s a gera&ccedil;&atilde;o de c&oacute;digo, ele corrige offsets de label para instru&ccedil;&otilde;es de desvio (<code>br</code>, <code>br_if</code>, <code>block</code>, <code>loop</code>). O linker tamb&eacute;m lida com a codifica&ccedil;&atilde;o da tabela de strings de nomes de exporta&ccedil;&atilde;o.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">A aloca&ccedil;&atilde;o de mem&oacute;ria usa um bump allocator embutido - <code>CRIA VETOR</code> com tamanhos conhecidos em tempo de compila&ccedil;&atilde;o emite <code>memory.grow</code> + aritm&eacute;tica de ponteiros. Strings s&atilde;o armazenadas como pares (comprimento, dados) no offset alocado.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">i32 / f64</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">Tipos de valor</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">block / loop</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">Fluxo de controle</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">call / return</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">Fun&ccedil;&otilde;es</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">memory.grow</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">Aloca&ccedil;&atilde;o din&acirc;mica</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ORM -->
<section id="orm" class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-center mb-3 sm:mb-4">ORM Integrado</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-500 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8 sm:mb-12 text-sm sm:text-lg font-light">Tabelas como um n&oacute; AST de primeira classe - analisadas, verificadas por tipo e geradas no pipeline do compilador.</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">XS</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto"><span class="kw">TABELA</span> <span class="fn">Product</span> {
  name: <span class="typ">TEXTO</span>,
  price: <span class="typ">NUMERO</span>,
  stock: <span class="typ">NUMERO</span>
}

<span class="kw">CRIA</span> repo = Product
repo.create({ name: <span class="str">&quot;Keyboard&quot;</span>, price: <span class="num">250</span>, stock: <span class="num">10</span> })
repo.create({ name: <span class="str">&quot;Mouse&quot;</span>, price: <span class="num">120</span>, stock: <span class="num">25</span> })

<span class="kw">SOLTA O GRITO</span>(repo.list())
<span class="kw">CRIA</span> expensive = repo.findWhere({ price: <span class="num">250</span> })
repo.update(<span class="num">1</span>, { name: <span class="str">&quot;RGB Keyboard&quot;</span> })
repo.delete(<span class="num">2</span>)</pre>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4"><code>TABELA</code> &eacute; analisado como um n&oacute; AST <code>TableDef</code> contendo um nome e uma lista de campos tipados. O parser valida que os tipos de campo s&atilde;o um dos cinco suportados: <code>TEXTO</code>, <code>NUMERO</code>, <code>BOOLEANO</code>, <code>DATA</code>, <code>QUALQUER</code>. Tipos inv&aacute;lidos produzem um erro em tempo de compila&ccedil;&atilde;o com anota&ccedil;&atilde;o de origem.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">No lado da gera&ccedil;&atilde;o de c&oacute;digo, <code>TableDef</code> emite uma fun&ccedil;&atilde;o construtora que retorna um objeto com os m&eacute;todos CRUD. O runtime armazena dados como arquivos JSON em disco (Node/Bun) ou em mem&oacute;ria (navegador). Cada registro recebe um campo <code>_id</code> auto-incrementado mais timestamps <code>_criado</code> e <code>_atualizado</code>.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">O m&eacute;todo <code>findWhere</code> suporta operadores de filtro passados como chaves prefixadas com <code>$</code>: <code>$eq</code>, <code>$gt</code>, <code>$lt</code>, <code>$gte</code>, <code>$lte</code>, <code>$ne</code> e <code>$in</code> (correspond&ecirc;ncia de array). Filtros compostos usam sem&acirc;ntica AND impl&iacute;cita.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">TEXTO</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">string</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">NUMERO</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">n&uacute;mero</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">BOOLEANO</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">booleano</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">DATA</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">string ISO</span></div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2.5 text-sm"><code class="text-pinky-500 font-mono text-xs">QUALQUER</code><span class="text-gray-400 text-xs">qualquer</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Macros -->
<section id="macros" class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-pinky-50/50">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-center mb-3 sm:mb-4">Macros em Tempo de Compila&ccedil;&atilde;o</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-500 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8 sm:mb-12 text-sm sm:text-lg font-light">Substitui&ccedil;&atilde;o em n&iacute;vel de AST - expandidas durante a fase de otimiza&ccedil;&atilde;o, removidas antes da gera&ccedil;&atilde;o de c&oacute;digo.</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">XS</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto"><span class="kw">MACRO</span> <span class="fn">square</span>(x) { x * x }
<span class="kw">MACRO</span> <span class="fn">cube</span>(x) { x * square(x) }
<span class="kw">MACRO</span> <span class="fn">max</span>(a, b) {
  <span class="kw">SE LIGA SO</span> (a > b) { a } <span class="kw">SENAO</span> { b }
}
<span class="kw">CRIA</span> r1 = square(<span class="num">5</span>)
<span class="kw">CRIA</span> r2 = cube(<span class="num">3</span>)
<span class="kw">CRIA</span> r3 = max(<span class="num">10</span>, <span class="num">20</span>)
<span class="kw">CRIA</span> r4 = max(square(<span class="num">4</span>), cube(<span class="num">2</span>))</pre>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">Macros s&atilde;o analisadas em n&oacute;s AST <code>MacroDef</code> com uma lista de par&acirc;metros e corpo. Durante a fase de otimiza&ccedil;&atilde;o, o expandidor de macros percorre a AST e substitui cada <code>CallExpr</code> que corresponde a um nome de macro pelo corpo da macro AST, substituindo identificadores de par&acirc;metros pelas express&otilde;es de argumento via c&oacute;pia superficial.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">A expans&atilde;o &eacute; <strong>recursiva</strong>: se um corpo de macro cont&eacute;m chamadas para outras macros, elas s&atilde;o expandidas em uma passagem p&oacute;s-substitui&ccedil;&atilde;o. O expandidor rastreia um contador de profundidade (limite padr&atilde;o: 64) para evitar recurs&atilde;o infinita de refer&ecirc;ncias circulares de macros. Ap&oacute;s a expans&atilde;o completa, todos os n&oacute;s <code>MacroDef</code> s&atilde;o removidos da AST.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">Como a expans&atilde;o opera na AST em vez de texto (diferente do pr&eacute;-processador C <code>#define</code>), n&atilde;o h&aacute; risco de bugs de preced&ecirc;ncia de operadores ou colagem n&atilde;o intencional de tokens. A AST resultante &eacute; ent&atilde;o alimentada pelo otimizador e gera&ccedil;&atilde;o de c&oacute;digo como se os corpos das macros fossem escritos inline.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Tests -->
<section id="tests" class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-center mb-3 sm:mb-4">Executor de Testes</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-500 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8 sm:mb-12 text-sm sm:text-lg font-light">N&oacute;s AST <code>TESTE</code> e <code>AFIRMA</code> de primeira classe - analisados, interpretados e relatados pelo pr&oacute;prio compilador.</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <div>
        <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">XS</div>
          <pre class="p-4 text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto"><span class="kw">TESTE</span> <span class="str">&quot;sum of two numbers&quot;</span> {
  <span class="kw">CRIA</span> r = <span class="num">2</span> + <span class="num">3</span>
  <span class="kw">AFIRMA</span>(r == <span class="num">5</span>)
  <span class="kw">ASSUNTO</span>(r, <span class="num">5</span>)
}
<span class="kw">TESTE</span> <span class="str">&quot;multiplication&quot;</span> {
  <span class="kw">CRIA</span> r = <span class="num">3</span> * <span class="num">4</span>
  <span class="kw">ASSUNTO</span>(r, <span class="num">12</span>)
}</pre>
        </div>
        <div data-cmd="xs test ." class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-sm text-gray-500 cursor-pointer transition-all hover:border-pinky-400 hover:shadow-sm select-none">
          <span class="text-pinky-400">$</span>
          <span class="text-gray-800">xs test .</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">Blocos <code>TESTE</code> s&atilde;o analisados em n&oacute;s AST <code>TestStmt</code> contendo uma express&atilde;o (a descri&ccedil;&atilde;o) e um bloco de instru&ccedil;&otilde;es. <code>AFIRMA</code> e <code>ASSUNTO</code> s&atilde;o analisados como n&oacute;s <code>AssertStmt</code> - o primeiro recebe uma &uacute;nica express&atilde;o booleana, o segundo recebe um par real/esperado com compara&ccedil;&atilde;o estrutural.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">O executor de testes descobre arquivos por padr&atilde;o glob (<code>**/*.test.xs</code>) e os executa atrav&eacute;s do interpretador AST. Cada <code>TestStmt</code> &eacute; envolvido em um try-catch: falhas de asser&ccedil;&atilde;o lan&ccedil;am objetos <code>AssertionError</code> estruturados com informa&ccedil;&otilde;es de arquivo/linha/diff. O executor agrega resultados e gera formato compat&iacute;vel com TAP com indicadores coloridos de passou/falhou, tempo de execu&ccedil;&atilde;o por teste e uma linha de resumo.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-4">C&oacute;digo de sa&iacute;da 1 em qualquer falha - pronto para CI/CD. A flag <code>xs test --watch</code> reexecuta ao detectar mudan&ccedil;as em arquivos usando o observador de arquivos embutido.</p>
        <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Sa&iacute;da</div>
          <pre class="p-4 text-green-600 text-xs sm:text-sm">  PASS  soma de dois n&uacute;meros (2ms)
  PASS  multiplica&ccedil;&atilde;o (1ms)

  Testes: 2 passaram, 2 total</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LSP -->
<section id="lsp" class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-pinky-50/50">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-center mb-3 sm:mb-4">LSP - Protocolo de Servidor de Linguagem</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-500 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-8 sm:mb-12 text-sm sm:text-lg font-light">Servidor LSP sem estado via stdin/stdout JSON-RPC - an&aacute;lise &uacute;nica por requisi&ccedil;&atilde;o, sem estado persistente.</p>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base mb-3">Inicie o servidor com <code class="bg-pinky-50">xs lsp</code>. Implementa <code>textDocument/completion</code> (itens de completa&ccedil;&atilde;o de palavra-chave/builtin/identificador com tipo e detalhe), <code>textDocument/hover</code> (documenta&ccedil;&atilde;o Markdown para fun&ccedil;&otilde;es embutidas com assinatura), <code>textDocument/definition</code> (resolve declara&ccedil;&otilde;es de vari&aacute;veis/fun&ccedil;&otilde;es para sua localiza&ccedil;&atilde;o de origem) e <code>textDocument/diagnostic</code> (sa&iacute;da completa de erro do compilador mapeada para Range, incluindo c&oacute;digo de erro e gravidade).</p>
        <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden mb-6">
          <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Bash</div>
          <pre class="p-4 text-xs sm:text-sm">xs lsp</pre>
        </div>
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-700 text-sm sm:text-base">Neovim</h4>
        <div class="code-block bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
          <pre class="p-4 text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto">vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(<span class="str">&quot;FileType&quot;</span>, {
  pattern = <span class="str">&quot;xs&quot;</span>,
  callback = <span class="kw">function</span>()
    vim.lsp.start({
      name = <span class="str">&quot;xanascript&quot;</span>,
